  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nIf I enable signature verification for initial sync, the sync gets stuck at slot 32, seems like the checkpoint epoch context is not correct to get proposer index, and we should rotate epoch.\r\n\r\nBut an additional epoch rotate is not a cheap at all as it loops through state validators (500ms to 600ms as far as I know for Pyrmont), we need to benchmark verifying signature signature set in batch vs. old flow (verify one by one) if we do that.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n+ Initial sync should get through epoch transition with signature verification\r\n+ make sure it logs out error, in this case it takes time to debug `beacon proposer index out of range` error\r\n<img width=\"944\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-12-10 at 09 01 58\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/101711700-afa9ab80-3ac6-11eb-88ce-f8c91535c144.png\">\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\nSync Peermont from scratch with signature verification\r\n",
